00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:14.681
HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
YEAR 1. CLASS 3

3
00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:31.489
YOON SE-A

4
00:00:31.573 --> 00:00:32.949
KIM U-JIN

5
00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:37.704
WE DO NOT CLIMB ON THE WINDOWS!

6
00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:44.669
OUR DREAMS

7
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:54.804
OUR AMAZING HAND TREE

8
00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:17.744
HOME OF THE HEART

9
00:01:19.996 --> 00:01:20.997
<i>Mom.</i>

10
00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:23.458
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

11
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:27.837
<i>I want to live.</i>

12
00:01:29.422 --> 00:01:31.591
<i>But to live. I think I need to die.</i>

13
00:01:34.385 --> 00:01:36.387
<i>You'll understand if you read my diary.</i>

14
00:01:41.184 --> 00:01:42.185
<i>Mom.</i>

15
00:01:44.312 --> 00:01:46.022
<i>Don't ever forgive that person.</i>

16
00:02:25.186 --> 00:02:26.312
Ms. Choi Ji-seon?

17
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.400
You must not have heard.

18
00:02:30.483 --> 00:02:33.069
The teachers have
a psychological evaluation today.

19
00:02:33.653 --> 00:02:36.698
It's almost time.
Please head over to the exam room.

20
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:48.001
You must have been tidying up.

21
00:02:51.629 --> 00:02:52.630
Yes.

22
00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:20.033
All elementary school teachers nationwide
will be taking part in this evaluation.

23
00:03:20.116 --> 00:03:23.286
The outcome will not result
in any disadvantages.

24
00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:25.955
So please complete it honestly.

25
00:03:28.082 --> 00:03:30.126
3. I'M DOING RELATIVELY WELL
NOT AT ALL

26
00:03:33.546 --> 00:03:35.590
<i>Have you been</i>
<i>to the Korean medicine clinic?</i>

27
00:03:37.217 --> 00:03:38.051
Pardon?

28
00:03:39.177 --> 00:03:40.428
About your face.

29
00:03:41.262 --> 00:03:43.139
It seems to have gotten worse.

30
00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:46.643
Ms. Choi.

31
00:03:47.143 --> 00:03:51.481
Following your psychological evaluation.
you will not be teaching from tomorrow.

32
00:03:52.857 --> 00:03:54.359
You said no disadvantages.

33
00:03:55.318 --> 00:03:57.779
There isn't a single
elementary school teacher

34
00:03:57.862 --> 00:04:00.198
who hasn't dealt with
stress or depression.

35
00:04:00.281 --> 00:04:03.326
You're basically telling her
to give up on being a teacher.

36
00:04:04.285 --> 00:04:05.328
But still.

37
00:04:05.411 --> 00:04:07.413
wouldn't it be better than dying?

38
00:04:15.713 --> 00:04:19.384
Ms. Choi. you will take
a temporary leave of absence

39
00:04:21.010 --> 00:04:22.679
as ordered by the ERPB.

40
00:04:29.352 --> 00:04:31.813
LET'S BECOME A GOOD TEACHER!

41
00:04:34.232 --> 00:04:35.942
TOMORROW I'LL MEET THE CHILDREN

42
00:04:36.025 --> 00:04:38.236
My daughter
is an elementary school teacher.

43
00:04:38.319 --> 00:04:39.529
UPHOLD U-JIN'S SELF-ESTEEM

44
00:04:39.612 --> 00:04:41.281
I was scared for her.

45
00:04:41.781 --> 00:04:45.368
These kinds of things were written
in her diary.

46
00:04:47.245 --> 00:04:50.290
Please save my daughter.

47
00:04:57.046 --> 00:05:01.134
WILL IT END IF I DIE?

48
00:05:01.217 --> 00:05:06.014
TEACH YOU A LESSON

49
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:08.266
HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

50
00:05:08.349 --> 00:05:11.602
What will happen to me now?

51
00:05:12.103 --> 00:05:13.896
You need to get treatment first.

52
00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:16.274
Your mother

53
00:05:16.357 --> 00:05:20.236
brought your things in earlier.

54
00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:23.114
Does my mom know… about this too?

55
00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:26.367
Your mother came to the ERPB.

56
00:05:27.785 --> 00:05:31.748
The best thing you can do for your mother
is to get good treatment.

57
00:05:31.831 --> 00:05:32.957
Shall we?

58
00:05:35.001 --> 00:05:38.629
Do you know what will happen
to my class and my students?

59
00:05:38.713 --> 00:05:41.966
Another teacher will take over from you.

60
00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:44.552
No. they can't.
Like me. that teacher will also--

61
00:05:44.635 --> 00:05:46.971
You don't have to worry about that.

62
00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:49.807
The new teacher

63
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:52.518
is extremely terrifying.

64
00:06:06.574 --> 00:06:08.242
NA HWA-JIN

65
00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:10.119
Everyone. shall we sit down?

66
00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.830
Attention!

67
00:06:12.914 --> 00:06:15.375
Kids. now's not the time for tag.

68
00:06:16.793 --> 00:06:17.919
Quiet!

69
00:06:21.506 --> 00:06:23.007
Class!

70
00:06:30.598 --> 00:06:31.682
Sir!

71
00:06:32.266 --> 00:06:36.229
If you and our tae kwon do master
got into a fight. who would win?

72
00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:38.272
Sir. can you beat Naruto?

73
00:06:38.356 --> 00:06:40.483
Sir. I need to use the bathroom.

74
00:06:40.566 --> 00:06:41.901
It's not bathroom time now.

75
00:06:41.984 --> 00:06:42.902
Sir.

76
00:06:42.985 --> 00:06:45.446
-I told you to wait. didn't I?
-Bathroom. sir.

77
00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:46.906
What's wrong? Huh?

78
00:06:46.989 --> 00:06:48.616
No. not your pants. Wait!

79
00:06:56.791 --> 00:06:57.708
Sir.

80
00:06:58.751 --> 00:06:59.961
Bathroom.

81
00:07:05.758 --> 00:07:07.051
Me too!

82
00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:11.139
Super fun!

83
00:07:12.181 --> 00:07:14.559
Yay. so fun!

84
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:17.770
You should have <i>gyeran-mari </i>for protein.

85
00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:19.188
-Don't you want it?
-Tomatoes.

86
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:21.524
Not a fan of tomatoes?

87
00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:27.738
Mr. Na.

88
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:28.948
Yes.

89
00:07:29.031 --> 00:07:30.032
Please fold me a frog.

90
00:07:30.116 --> 00:07:33.119
It's not time to fold frogs.
Just do what I asked you to do.

91
00:07:33.202 --> 00:07:34.912
Please fold one for me.

92
00:07:34.996 --> 00:07:37.999
It's not time for frogs right now.
Just do as you're told.

93
00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.339
No. I wasn't mad at you.

94
00:07:45.840 --> 00:07:47.758
We flip this over again.

95
00:07:50.344 --> 00:07:52.513
Okay. just like this.

96
00:07:53.055 --> 00:07:55.558
It's the shape of a frog's back legs.

97
00:07:55.641 --> 00:07:57.894
Yeon-seo. have you tried frog legs before?

98
00:07:57.977 --> 00:08:00.104
Yuck. Do people eat frog legs?

99
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:01.814
I've tried them before.

100
00:08:01.898 --> 00:08:04.525
The frog is done!

101
00:08:04.609 --> 00:08:06.486
Hop! Wow.

102
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:08.654
Make one for me too. please!

103
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:30.301
Ga-yun.

104
00:08:30.801 --> 00:08:33.054
Was being a teacher this hard?

105
00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:40.269
Those damn frogs. I had to…

106
00:08:52.406 --> 00:08:53.824
LET'S BECOME A GOOD TEACHER!

107
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:58.162
<i>Today. we're going to learn</i>
<i>how to express our feelings with words.</i>

108
00:08:58.246 --> 00:09:02.166
What do you say when you're feeling happy?

109
00:09:03.751 --> 00:09:04.627
That's right.

110
00:09:04.710 --> 00:09:07.338
"I'm in a good mood. I'm so happy."

111
00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.967
Just like this. we need to be able
to put our feelings into words.

112
00:09:11.050 --> 00:09:15.137
You always have to tell me
how you're feeling.

113
00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:16.264
Okay?

114
00:09:16.347 --> 00:09:19.684
It's nice to meet you. My name is…

115
00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:26.524
CHOI JI-SEON

116
00:09:31.654 --> 00:09:32.738
Class!

117
00:09:32.822 --> 00:09:34.615
It's nice to meet you.

118
00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:37.785
My name is Choi Ji-seon.

119
00:09:40.496 --> 00:09:42.540
I hope we can get along well.

120
00:09:42.623 --> 00:09:44.083
You know who I am now. right?

121
00:09:44.667 --> 00:09:48.129
Can you please
introduce yourselves to me too?

122
00:09:48.212 --> 00:09:50.298
Yes!

123
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:51.215
You can start.

124
00:09:52.592 --> 00:09:54.802
I am Kim Yong-hun.

125
00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:58.556
I am Lee Yeon-seo.

126
00:10:13.988 --> 00:10:15.239
You're Kim U-jin. right?

127
00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:17.366
It's all right. Take a seat.

128
00:10:18.784 --> 00:10:19.744
Applause.

129
00:10:23.039 --> 00:10:24.707
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

130
00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:27.376
-Bye. Thank you.
-Thank you.

131
00:10:27.460 --> 00:10:28.711
Take care. ma'am.

132
00:10:28.794 --> 00:10:30.087
See you tomorrow. U-jin.

133
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:31.839
-Say goodbye. Hun.
-Goodbye.

134
00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:34.425
Please take good care of U-jin. Ms. Choi.

135
00:10:34.508 --> 00:10:36.802
I'll do my best.
You can trust me with him.

136
00:10:37.386 --> 00:10:41.641
If I have any questions or concerns
from time to time. may I contact you?

137
00:10:41.724 --> 00:10:42.933
Of course you can.

138
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:45.811
If you install the Talk Mate app.
you can message or call me.

139
00:10:45.895 --> 00:10:49.190
Please contact me there.
The hours are from eight to six.

140
00:10:50.149 --> 00:10:52.068
You live in Stern Complex. don't you?

141
00:10:53.069 --> 00:10:54.487
Yes. I do.

142
00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:57.948
Thanks for today. Let's go. U-jin.

143
00:11:09.418 --> 00:11:12.963
<i>This is U-jin's mom.</i>
<i>I have a small concern.</i>

144
00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:17.968
<i>When you told U-jin to sit earlier.</i>
<i>you spoke very sternly.</i>

145
00:11:18.052 --> 00:11:22.306
<i>I'm worried U-jin might think</i>
<i>you don't like him.</i>

146
00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:24.892
<i>I'll do my best to make sure</i>
<i>he doesn't feel that way.</i>

147
00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:33.275
<i>I'm just worried his self-esteem</i>
<i>might drop. You understand. right?</i>

148
00:11:34.610 --> 00:11:35.444
Of course.

149
00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:39.573
<i>Request for Kim U-jin.</i>
<i>Make sure his self-esteem isn't affected.</i>

150
00:11:50.793 --> 00:11:52.461
You're not sure?

151
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.088
Should I explain again?

152
00:11:55.214 --> 00:11:57.216
Ms. Choi. I want to do it.

153
00:11:57.299 --> 00:11:58.801
I can do it too!

154
00:11:58.884 --> 00:12:00.511
I can do it too!

155
00:12:00.594 --> 00:12:02.221
Quiet.

156
00:12:06.934 --> 00:12:07.768
It's all right.

157
00:12:13.190 --> 00:12:14.984
<i>U-jin's self-esteem is falling.</i>

158
00:12:15.067 --> 00:12:17.486
<i>so don't make him do math</i>
<i>in front of the class.</i>

159
00:12:20.614 --> 00:12:24.118
<i>Please don't mark incorrect answers</i>
<i>with a slash on U-jin's spelling test.</i>

160
00:12:24.201 --> 00:12:25.953
<i>It's affecting his self-esteem.</i>

161
00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:32.668
<i>"Don't." "no." or "stop."</i>
<i>Please don't use these restrictive words.</i>

162
00:12:34.336 --> 00:12:37.965
<i>Please always take my child's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers.</i>

163
00:12:38.048 --> 00:12:41.969
<i>Please use an advisory or requesting tone</i>
<i>rather than a commanding one.</i>

164
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:45.181
<i>When greeting. please don't make him bow</i>
<i>with his hands together.</i>

165
00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:48.893
<i>If he feels pressured to greet properly.</i>
<i>it will lower his self-esteem.</i>

166
00:12:48.976 --> 00:12:52.062
<i>Please don't scold children</i>
<i>for being noisy in the classroom.</i>

167
00:12:52.146 --> 00:12:53.814
<i>It will make them feel discouraged.</i>

168
00:13:18.172 --> 00:13:19.423
-You're overreacting.
-Yeah.

169
00:13:19.507 --> 00:13:21.175
-It's Ji-seon.
-Ji-seon!

170
00:13:23.302 --> 00:13:24.970
-I've missed you.
-It's been so long.

171
00:13:25.054 --> 00:13:25.888
Ji-seon.

172
00:13:29.642 --> 00:13:31.727
-Congratulations!
-When is the wedding?

173
00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:33.938
-It's written in there. Take a look.
-Hold on.

174
00:13:34.021 --> 00:13:35.689
Won-ho can't seem to stop smiling.

175
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.691
<i>Please wear a strapless bra.</i>

176
00:13:37.775 --> 00:13:40.444
<i>It may negatively affect</i>
<i>the boys' sexual awareness.</i>

177
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:42.446
-Congratulations. Won-ho!
-Cheers!

178
00:13:42.530 --> 00:13:44.782
Cheers!

179
00:14:00.422 --> 00:14:03.968
<i>Why would you post something shameful</i>
<i>when the children might see it?</i>

180
00:14:04.051 --> 00:14:06.637
<i>I'm afraid it might provoke</i>
<i>their sexual curiosity.</i>

181
00:14:11.225 --> 00:14:13.769
How did she find my Instagram?

182
00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:16.522
<i>You always seem to be out.</i>
<i>Don't you think of the children?</i>

183
00:14:16.605 --> 00:14:18.941
<i>You spend your tax-funded salary</i>
<i>on having fun.</i>

184
00:14:19.024 --> 00:14:21.277
<i>Please invest in preparing for class too.</i>

185
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:24.071
<i>I'd tolerate it</i>
<i>if it were at least about children.</i>

186
00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:27.366
But I think she's gone too far.
It's strictly personal.

187
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:31.036
Change your account username.

188
00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:33.539
Actually. it'd be even better
if you didn't use it.

189
00:14:33.622 --> 00:14:35.791
Why should I?
I haven't done anything wrong.

190
00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:38.460
I tried to take action at first too.

191
00:14:38.544 --> 00:14:40.754
I tried pressing charges
and persuading them.

192
00:14:40.838 --> 00:14:43.465
But in the end.
all I got was a group petition

193
00:14:43.549 --> 00:14:45.593
claiming I sided only with the teachers.

194
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:48.846
No matter what I said.
they wouldn't listen.

195
00:14:48.929 --> 00:14:51.348
And no matter what I did.
they saw it negatively.

196
00:14:51.432 --> 00:14:53.475
In the end. they shook up

197
00:14:53.976 --> 00:14:55.269
the whole school.

198
00:15:02.026 --> 00:15:03.777
REMOVE "INSTAGRAM"?
DELETE APP

199
00:15:04.278 --> 00:15:05.696
DELETE "INSTAGRAM"?
DELETE

200
00:15:12.244 --> 00:15:15.247
<i>I'll use Instagram when I retire.</i>

201
00:15:15.748 --> 00:15:18.709
<i>I have the children to consider.</i>

202
00:16:15.933 --> 00:16:18.227
HOME OF THE HEART

203
00:16:52.928 --> 00:16:53.762
U-jin.

204
00:16:55.556 --> 00:16:58.475
This is your Home of the Heart.

205
00:16:58.559 --> 00:17:00.728
You can have fun with your friends here.

206
00:17:06.358 --> 00:17:08.110
How do you feel?

207
00:17:08.610 --> 00:17:10.446
What do you look for in a friend?

208
00:17:11.905 --> 00:17:13.949
I want to have fun together.

209
00:17:14.450 --> 00:17:15.451
Right?

210
00:17:15.534 --> 00:17:19.580
Since this is Home of the Heart.
you can do whatever your heart tells you.

211
00:17:20.080 --> 00:17:21.331
Should we try to do

212
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:23.834
what your heart is telling you?

213
00:17:28.255 --> 00:17:29.673
Oh. it's the back.

214
00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:34.636
Yes!

215
00:17:35.512 --> 00:17:36.638
Here's water.

216
00:17:36.722 --> 00:17:37.848
Thanks.

217
00:17:43.395 --> 00:17:45.481
-Don't hurt yourself.
-Go. U-jin!

218
00:17:45.564 --> 00:17:46.523
Whoa!

219
00:17:49.109 --> 00:17:49.943
U-jin. well done!

220
00:17:50.027 --> 00:17:51.070
Yeah!

221
00:17:51.153 --> 00:17:52.362
Over here. Pass!

222
00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:55.824
Eun-ho kicks the ball.

223
00:17:55.908 --> 00:17:57.284
Over here. Pass!

224
00:17:57.993 --> 00:17:59.244
U-jin. pass!

225
00:18:01.246 --> 00:18:02.539
Hey. it went in.

226
00:18:03.707 --> 00:18:05.709
U-jin. I'm sorry.

227
00:18:08.212 --> 00:18:10.214
-Kim U-jin!
-<i>"Don't." "no." or "stop."</i>

228
00:18:10.297 --> 00:18:12.674
<i>Please don't use these restrictive words.</i>

229
00:18:13.175 --> 00:18:16.804
<i>Please always take my child's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers.</i>

230
00:18:18.806 --> 00:18:20.933
That hurts.

231
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:22.059
Mommy.

232
00:18:22.142 --> 00:18:23.435
U-jin!

233
00:18:25.229 --> 00:18:31.026
Mommy!

234
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:34.113
-It hurts.
-Seo-jun. are you okay?

235
00:18:34.863 --> 00:18:36.907
Mommy.

236
00:18:39.952 --> 00:18:41.453
Ladies.

237
00:18:42.371 --> 00:18:44.039
I'm sure you were alarmed.

238
00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:45.999
Please have some tea first.

239
00:18:54.800 --> 00:18:58.387
Seo-jun briefly told me what happened.

240
00:18:59.221 --> 00:19:02.432
They're boys. and when they play sports.

241
00:19:04.059 --> 00:19:05.519
they can get into fights.

242
00:19:05.602 --> 00:19:06.478
I understand.

243
00:19:06.562 --> 00:19:08.981
Thank you for understanding.

244
00:19:09.064 --> 00:19:12.151
The children apologized
to each other and made up.

245
00:19:13.402 --> 00:19:15.279
Did you make U-jin apologize?

246
00:19:21.201 --> 00:19:23.745
He did something wrong.
Of course he has to apologize.

247
00:19:23.829 --> 00:19:27.457
U-jin told me Seo-jun pushed him first.

248
00:19:27.958 --> 00:19:30.419
Since Seo-jun started it.
only he should apologize.

249
00:19:32.963 --> 00:19:34.006
Ma'am.

250
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:36.633
Seo-jun injured his eye.

251
00:19:36.717 --> 00:19:38.427
He almost went blind.

252
00:19:38.510 --> 00:19:40.596
U-jin was also hurt.

253
00:19:40.679 --> 00:19:43.640
He was so upset
that he came home and cried.

254
00:19:43.724 --> 00:19:46.101
You have a strange way of putting things.

255
00:19:46.185 --> 00:19:49.021
Can't you see I'm trying to let it go
for our kids' sake?

256
00:19:49.104 --> 00:19:50.814
My child's feelings got hurt!

257
00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:53.650
What will you do if he's traumatized?

258
00:19:53.734 --> 00:19:56.904
He'd better not be.
I won't let your son get away with it.

259
00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:58.947
-What?
-Ladies.

260
00:19:59.031 --> 00:20:00.616
Please stop. and let's calm down.

261
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:03.076
Ms. Choi. please say something.

262
00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:06.914
I heard U-jin couldn't even get along
with others in the beginning.

263
00:20:06.997 --> 00:20:09.124
Now I can see why.

264
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:10.459
-Hey!
-"Hey"?

265
00:20:10.959 --> 00:20:13.795
Convene the School Violence Committee.
Try mouthing off there.

266
00:20:13.879 --> 00:20:15.672
All right. Fine!

267
00:20:15.756 --> 00:20:17.090
Bring it on. Convene it!

268
00:20:17.174 --> 00:20:21.303
Ladies. please calm down.
I'm begging you. Please calm down.

269
00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:22.804
Ma'am.

270
00:20:23.305 --> 00:20:26.892
I feel a School Violence Committee meeting
would be unfavorable for U-jin.

271
00:20:26.975 --> 00:20:28.143
Why don't we all just--

272
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:30.812
Things have been blown out of proportion
because of you.

273
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:35.692
I told you to take U-jin's side
in any conflicts with his peers.

274
00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:37.194
and you agreed to it.

275
00:20:37.903 --> 00:20:39.863
I never agreed to it.

276
00:20:41.531 --> 00:20:42.449
Pardon me?

277
00:20:43.533 --> 00:20:47.246
Why claim now you never agreed
when you were silent back then?

278
00:20:47.955 --> 00:20:50.123
I will speak to Seo-jun's mother--

279
00:20:50.207 --> 00:20:51.959
How will you testify at the meeting?

280
00:20:54.753 --> 00:20:55.921
Well…

281
00:20:57.339 --> 00:20:59.758
-I'll have to tell them what I saw.
-Right.

282
00:21:00.884 --> 00:21:02.302
So what did you see?

283
00:21:09.393 --> 00:21:10.560
Give me your number.

284
00:21:10.644 --> 00:21:13.355
It's against policy
to give out our personal phone numbers.

285
00:21:13.438 --> 00:21:15.857
-On Talk Mate--
-I can't call you there after work.

286
00:21:15.941 --> 00:21:18.318
You still want to enjoy
your post-work life

287
00:21:18.402 --> 00:21:20.362
after getting my child into trouble?

288
00:21:20.445 --> 00:21:21.655
That's not what I mean.

289
00:21:21.738 --> 00:21:22.990
Give it to me!

290
00:21:31.206 --> 00:21:33.166
This is all your fault.

291
00:21:34.376 --> 00:21:35.502
Do you know what?

292
00:21:36.003 --> 00:21:38.588
My husband is furious about this.

293
00:21:39.089 --> 00:21:41.758
Should I call him right now? Should I?

294
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:44.428
Ma'am.

295
00:21:45.470 --> 00:21:48.432
A homeroom teacher
cannot help you in that way.

296
00:22:05.532 --> 00:22:06.366
Hello?

297
00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:07.743
<i>This is U-jin's mom.</i>

298
00:22:08.744 --> 00:22:09.745
Ma'am.

299
00:22:10.537 --> 00:22:12.289
How did you get my number?

300
00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:15.792
<i>Is that important right now?</i>
<i>What are you going to do at the meeting?</i>

301
00:22:18.003 --> 00:22:19.379
<i>Hello? Answer me.</i>

302
00:22:19.463 --> 00:22:20.380
Well…

303
00:22:20.464 --> 00:22:22.090
U-JIN'S MOTHER

304
00:22:31.933 --> 00:22:32.893
<i>Hello?</i>

305
00:22:33.393 --> 00:22:34.227
<i>Ms. Choi!</i>

306
00:22:34.311 --> 00:22:35.520
Hello?

307
00:22:35.604 --> 00:22:37.898
<i>Why did you take so long to answer?</i>

308
00:22:38.899 --> 00:22:39.900
<i>Hello?</i>

309
00:22:42.152 --> 00:22:43.653
I'm sorry.

310
00:22:43.737 --> 00:22:45.364
U-JIN'S MOTHER

311
00:22:47.532 --> 00:22:48.742
<i>Are you listening to me?</i>

312
00:22:49.493 --> 00:22:50.952
<i>Why aren't you answering me?</i>

313
00:22:51.036 --> 00:22:54.081
I'm planning my lessons at the moment.

314
00:22:55.457 --> 00:22:56.625
U-JIN'S MOTHER

315
00:23:06.426 --> 00:23:08.637
U-JIN'S MOTHER

316
00:23:10.722 --> 00:23:11.973
U-JIN'S MOTHER

317
00:23:13.934 --> 00:23:16.853
<i>I told you to take U-jin's side</i>
<i>in any conflicts with his peers.</i>

318
00:23:16.937 --> 00:23:18.021
<i>and you agreed to it.</i>

319
00:23:18.105 --> 00:23:20.357
<i>You still want to enjoy</i>
<i>your post-work life</i>

320
00:23:20.440 --> 00:23:22.526
<i>after getting my child into trouble?</i>

321
00:23:24.611 --> 00:23:25.487
U-JIN'S MOTHER

322
00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:27.489
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

323
00:23:27.572 --> 00:23:30.158
<i>And you agreed to it.</i>

324
00:23:31.076 --> 00:23:32.077
<i>Ms. Choi?</i>

325
00:23:33.078 --> 00:23:34.162
<i>Ms. Choi?</i>

326
00:23:39.751 --> 00:23:41.461
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

327
00:23:41.545 --> 00:23:45.549
<i>This is all your fault now.</i>

328
00:23:45.632 --> 00:23:47.926
<i>Ms. Choi!</i>

329
00:24:05.569 --> 00:24:06.820
<i>Ms. Choi.</i>

330
00:24:06.903 --> 00:24:09.030
<i>Why aren't you answering your phone?</i>

331
00:24:09.114 --> 00:24:10.991
<i>Are you avoiding me out of guilt?</i>

332
00:24:11.741 --> 00:24:13.452
<i>Let's talk in person.</i>

333
00:24:13.535 --> 00:24:14.536
-<i>Okay?</i>
-Who is it?

334
00:24:17.789 --> 00:24:19.791
I'm just going out for a moment.

335
00:24:19.875 --> 00:24:20.792
Where to?

336
00:24:22.961 --> 00:24:24.296
Where are you going?

337
00:24:25.505 --> 00:24:27.716
This is absurd.
How is U-jin the perpetrator?

338
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:29.384
It's unacceptable.

339
00:24:29.468 --> 00:24:31.887
Why did the School Violence Committee
rule against us?

340
00:24:32.637 --> 00:24:34.181
It's Level 1 disciplinary action.

341
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.516
All you need to do
is submit a written apology.

342
00:24:36.600 --> 00:24:38.059
It was you. wasn't it?

343
00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:40.896
-Pardon?
-You took their side. didn't you?

344
00:24:41.938 --> 00:24:43.815
You're mistaken. I didn't side with--

345
00:24:43.899 --> 00:24:45.984
Just because I said a few things.

346
00:24:46.067 --> 00:24:48.320
you went after U-jin out of spite.
didn't you?

347
00:24:52.782 --> 00:24:55.869
You don't deserve to be a teacher.

348
00:24:57.162 --> 00:24:59.789
I can't trust you with U-jin anymore.
so just quit.

349
00:24:59.873 --> 00:25:02.417
My husband is also enraged.

350
00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:04.336
so watch out.

351
00:25:37.702 --> 00:25:38.537
Dad?

352
00:25:50.173 --> 00:25:51.383
U-jin. come with me.

353
00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:54.553
Come on. Kim U-jin.

354
00:25:59.516 --> 00:26:00.517
I said come with me!

355
00:26:01.434 --> 00:26:03.770
We're in class right now.
If you come back later…

356
00:26:08.817 --> 00:26:11.403
Please don't do this. Think of U-jin.

357
00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:18.118
For God's sake.

358
00:26:18.785 --> 00:26:20.287
How pathetic. Seriously.

359
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:24.332
Let's go.

360
00:26:25.166 --> 00:26:26.001
Move.

361
00:26:33.258 --> 00:26:34.509
Everyone. it's all right.

362
00:26:37.137 --> 00:26:38.763
It's okay. Ji-yeong. Don't cry.

363
00:26:45.353 --> 00:26:49.274
TEACHERS' RIGHTS PROTECTION COMMITTEE
NOTICE TO ATTEND

364
00:26:54.946 --> 00:26:56.364
<i>Do it if you want to.</i>

365
00:26:56.865 --> 00:27:00.285
Even if I violated teachers' rights.
all I have to do is apologize.

366
00:27:00.785 --> 00:27:02.454
Call a meeting on teachers' rights.

367
00:27:05.081 --> 00:27:08.126
I couldn't just sit back
when you abused your power.

368
00:27:12.547 --> 00:27:14.549
So I reported you for child abuse.

369
00:27:17.761 --> 00:27:20.722
You targeted U-jin.
humiliating him in front of others.

370
00:27:20.805 --> 00:27:24.267
And when I challenged this.
you gaslit a student to ostracize him.

371
00:27:24.351 --> 00:27:27.187
You lured him to a storage room
you call Home of the Heart

372
00:27:27.270 --> 00:27:28.647
and did unspeakable things--

373
00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:31.149
Ma'am. none of this is true.

374
00:27:31.232 --> 00:27:33.610
It's up to the police to look into that.

375
00:27:33.693 --> 00:27:36.446
Ma'am. I have never
emotionally abused a child.

376
00:27:38.073 --> 00:27:41.660
Do you think I made up a story
just to screw you over?

377
00:27:42.786 --> 00:27:44.788
What about how wronged U-jin feels?

378
00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:49.250
If you're innocent.
then why is U-jin crying at home?

379
00:27:49.334 --> 00:27:51.294
I feel for U-jin.

380
00:27:51.961 --> 00:27:53.171
but this isn't right.

381
00:27:53.254 --> 00:27:55.590
So why is the teacher
not taking responsibility

382
00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:57.717
when a student has been wronged?

383
00:27:57.801 --> 00:27:59.511
Is it my resignation

384
00:28:00.011 --> 00:28:01.346
that you want?

385
00:28:02.263 --> 00:28:04.099
I also consulted a lawyer.

386
00:28:04.182 --> 00:28:06.309
The law has changed.
Even if you report me.

387
00:28:06.810 --> 00:28:09.437
I won't be suspended immediately
like before.

388
00:28:09.521 --> 00:28:10.980
Who said anything about that?

389
00:28:11.481 --> 00:28:12.482
Teach your class.

390
00:28:12.565 --> 00:28:15.318
When you're done.
give your statement to the police.

391
00:28:16.027 --> 00:28:18.488
Reaching a verdict
will take six months to a year.

392
00:28:18.571 --> 00:28:20.240
It'll take longer than you think.

393
00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:22.450
If you can't handle it. you can quit.

394
00:28:29.708 --> 00:28:32.460
If I'm found innocent.
what will you do then?

395
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:38.717
Then I'll have to apologize.

396
00:28:39.759 --> 00:28:40.885
That's all.

397
00:28:41.386 --> 00:28:42.762
That's the law.

398
00:29:19.132 --> 00:29:20.175
<i>Ms. Choi.</i>

399
00:29:20.258 --> 00:29:23.344
<i>This came up on a moms' forum.</i>
<i>Have you seen it?</i>

400
00:29:23.428 --> 00:29:25.638
<i>It seems quite serious.</i>

401
00:29:26.848 --> 00:29:29.642
1-3 HOMEROOM TEACHER
AT HYEONJUNG ELEMENTARY IS A CHILD ABUSER

402
00:29:32.103 --> 00:29:33.605
LOOKS CAN BE DECEIVING
SO SHOCKING

403
00:29:35.732 --> 00:29:38.485
PLEASE SHARE THIS POST UNTIL THE DAY
CHOI JI-SEON IS PUNISHED

404
00:29:38.568 --> 00:29:39.611
MS. CHOI 010-0235-7462

405
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:53.708
All right. Year 1. class 3.
please come in.

406
00:29:55.877 --> 00:29:56.795
Let's go. class.

407
00:30:02.967 --> 00:30:04.135
Have a watermelon slice.

408
00:30:10.683 --> 00:30:12.477
Is that all the rice you're having?

409
00:30:12.977 --> 00:30:15.063
Is that okay? Enjoy your meal.

410
00:30:16.981 --> 00:30:17.816
Scissors.

411
00:30:18.775 --> 00:30:20.568
Scissors. scissors. rock.

412
00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:24.364
<i>We keep getting complaint calls.</i>

413
00:30:25.281 --> 00:30:27.826
<i>Many parents are coming in person too.</i>

414
00:30:28.743 --> 00:30:30.578
<i>They say if we let you come to work.</i>

415
00:30:31.329 --> 00:30:33.498
<i>they won't send their children to school.</i>

416
00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:37.293
<i>I'm sorry</i>

417
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:40.129
<i>I can't tell you to hold out.</i>

418
00:31:20.169 --> 00:31:22.171
{\an8}TEACHER
KIM U-JIN

419
00:31:26.009 --> 00:31:28.219
KIDDOS IN YEAR 1. CLASS 3

420
00:31:28.303 --> 00:31:29.721
KIM U-JIN: THOUGHTFUL. SMILEY

421
00:31:29.804 --> 00:31:31.139
KIM YUN-U: VERY CONSIDERATE

422
00:31:36.519 --> 00:31:39.647
MS. CHOI. BE HAPPY

423
00:31:43.401 --> 00:31:46.362
<i>She would've felt like</i>
<i>she was standing all alone in a jungle.</i>

424
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:48.531
IT'S HARD TO OPEN MY EYES IN THE MORNING

425
00:31:49.115 --> 00:31:50.867
Eyes were on her from all sides.

426
00:31:51.367 --> 00:31:54.203
with people ready to pounce on her.

427
00:31:55.747 --> 00:31:57.624
There was no one or weapon to help her.

428
00:31:57.707 --> 00:31:59.417
I'M MAKING MY OWN STUDENTS UNHAPPY

429
00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:00.335
WILL IT END IF I DIE?

430
00:32:00.418 --> 00:32:02.253
Why are the police investigating this?

431
00:32:02.337 --> 00:32:04.839
It's all perfectly reasonable
and legitimate guidance.

432
00:32:05.423 --> 00:32:08.009
The police have to investigate
since a report was filed.

433
00:32:08.092 --> 00:32:10.595
Can they report it
when it's clearly unreasonable?

434
00:32:10.678 --> 00:32:12.138
Yes. they can.

435
00:32:12.221 --> 00:32:13.348
They can?

436
00:32:13.431 --> 00:32:16.434
For child abuse. you can file a report
based solely on suspicion.

437
00:32:18.686 --> 00:32:19.938
As you can see.

438
00:32:20.021 --> 00:32:24.817
11.626 teachers
have been reported for child abuse

439
00:32:24.901 --> 00:32:27.362
over the past several years.

440
00:32:27.445 --> 00:32:30.281
But only 1.6% of them

441
00:32:30.365 --> 00:32:32.075
were actually prosecuted.

442
00:32:32.951 --> 00:32:37.622
This means most of the teachers suffered
because of the reports.

443
00:32:38.247 --> 00:32:41.292
even though their guidance was legitimate.

444
00:32:41.376 --> 00:32:44.212
Since you can report
based on suspicion alone.

445
00:32:44.712 --> 00:32:48.007
you won't be punished
for a false accusation

446
00:32:48.091 --> 00:32:49.926
even if the accused is found innocent.

447
00:32:50.468 --> 00:32:52.387
That's what the parents are abusing.

448
00:32:52.470 --> 00:32:53.888
They press charges first.

449
00:32:54.764 --> 00:32:56.933
and if the verdict is innocent.
they dismiss it.

450
00:32:57.016 --> 00:32:58.142
Damn it.

451
00:32:58.226 --> 00:33:02.981
Emotional abuse is difficult to define
under current child abuse laws

452
00:33:03.064 --> 00:33:04.941
because the harm isn't visible.

453
00:33:06.275 --> 00:33:08.403
You can only rely on what the parents say.

454
00:33:08.486 --> 00:33:10.863
It's difficult for teachers
to prove it's not abuse.

455
00:33:10.947 --> 00:33:12.949
And they get worn down alone.

456
00:33:13.032 --> 00:33:15.284
Most of them will be found innocent.

457
00:33:15.368 --> 00:33:17.954
but until then.
they have to be investigated

458
00:33:18.037 --> 00:33:20.415
and. in some cases.
be removed from their class.

459
00:33:20.498 --> 00:33:24.752
Teachers are told not to hit. even gently.
yet parents are effectively handed guns.

460
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:27.839
What are teachers supposed
to block the bullets with?

461
00:33:27.922 --> 00:33:29.257
Seriously!

462
00:33:30.049 --> 00:33:30.883
Damn it.

463
00:33:31.384 --> 00:33:32.427
In the current system.

464
00:33:33.052 --> 00:33:36.806
if teachers are reported for child abuse.

465
00:33:36.889 --> 00:33:38.933
there's basically no shield
to protect them.

466
00:33:43.771 --> 00:33:44.897
We can be

467
00:33:45.815 --> 00:33:47.025
their shield.

468
00:33:47.692 --> 00:33:49.068
Although it will be difficult.

469
00:33:50.153 --> 00:33:51.195
we'll go step by step.

470
00:33:52.447 --> 00:33:53.573
That's what we'll do.

471
00:33:55.158 --> 00:33:56.409
So. Na Hwa-jin.

472
00:33:56.492 --> 00:34:00.371
You just handle the power-abusing parents
hiding behind the law.

473
00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:14.677
I'm getting all fired up to fight.

474
00:34:14.761 --> 00:34:16.054
You've got this!

475
00:34:16.137 --> 00:34:20.183
"You just handle the power-abusing parents
hiding behind the law."

476
00:34:24.771 --> 00:34:25.730
Ms. Choi Ji-seon.

477
00:34:26.230 --> 00:34:27.815
Please come this way.

478
00:34:27.899 --> 00:34:29.067
COUNSELING ROOM

479
00:34:31.319 --> 00:34:32.236
I'll see you soon.

480
00:34:42.997 --> 00:34:46.667
How can a person
harass someone to this extent?

481
00:34:46.751 --> 00:34:48.503
I think people are the scariest.

482
00:34:49.504 --> 00:34:53.341
Still. reptilians are a little scarier.

483
00:34:53.424 --> 00:34:54.258
Rep… what?

484
00:34:54.342 --> 00:34:58.137
There are actually aliens
who have infiltrated Earth right now.

485
00:34:58.221 --> 00:34:59.764
Aliens do not exist.

486
00:34:59.847 --> 00:35:02.892
They really do. There is various evidence
to show reptilian aliens--

487
00:35:02.975 --> 00:35:04.852
Seriously. you believe in strange things.

488
00:35:07.980 --> 00:35:11.859
Okay. fine. I'll stop talking now.

489
00:35:12.443 --> 00:35:13.986
Why?

490
00:35:14.070 --> 00:35:16.155
Do I not seem worth talking to anymore?

491
00:35:16.239 --> 00:35:19.617
It feels like my loss

492
00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:22.370
when I talk to people
who are a little ignorant.

493
00:35:22.954 --> 00:35:23.788
I see.

494
00:35:23.871 --> 00:35:25.623
Deputy Director Bong.

495
00:35:25.706 --> 00:35:26.541
Yes?

496
00:35:26.624 --> 00:35:28.334
-The rep…
-Reptilians.

497
00:35:29.001 --> 00:35:31.379
Right. the rep… whatever.

498
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:32.839
Yes?

499
00:35:33.464 --> 00:35:36.050
Should I show you
that people are scarier than them?

500
00:35:36.759 --> 00:35:37.718
No…

501
00:35:43.683 --> 00:35:44.517
Look.

502
00:35:45.476 --> 00:35:48.855
I'll show you again how to write
the Chinese character for "patience."

503
00:35:48.938 --> 00:35:50.606
It starts with "do" for knife.

504
00:35:51.107 --> 00:35:52.483
Then "sim" for heart.

505
00:35:53.067 --> 00:35:54.777
Cut your heart with a knife.

506
00:35:55.486 --> 00:35:56.362
Try to…

507
00:36:20.094 --> 00:36:23.389
All right.
who would like to solve this problem?

508
00:36:23.472 --> 00:36:24.515
-Me!
-Me!

509
00:36:29.896 --> 00:36:31.063
U-jin. you can try.

510
00:36:35.860 --> 00:36:41.282
<i>In math class. we solved problems</i>
<i>on the board with friends.</i>

511
00:36:41.365 --> 00:36:42.909
<i>Although we taught them.</i>

512
00:36:42.992 --> 00:36:46.996
<i>if anything still needs work.</i>
<i>please review it at home.</i>

513
00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:01.177
Oh my God!

514
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:04.305
Are you all right?

515
00:37:05.681 --> 00:37:08.434
-Let me help you.
-Why were you standing there?

516
00:37:08.517 --> 00:37:10.102
Well…

517
00:37:10.603 --> 00:37:14.523
This is my classroom.
and I'm the homeroom teacher.

518
00:37:15.942 --> 00:37:18.569
Are you U-jin's new homeroom teacher?

519
00:37:18.653 --> 00:37:20.529
You must be U-jin's mother.

520
00:37:21.113 --> 00:37:23.199
Hello. ma'am.

521
00:37:23.282 --> 00:37:25.785
I'm Na Hwa-jin. U-jin's homeroom teacher.

522
00:37:25.868 --> 00:37:28.579
What brings you here
this early in the morning?

523
00:37:28.663 --> 00:37:31.499
Yesterday. you made U-jin
solve math problems. didn't you?

524
00:37:31.582 --> 00:37:33.876
Yes. but I was so surprised.

525
00:37:33.960 --> 00:37:36.796
How is U-jin so smart?

526
00:37:36.879 --> 00:37:39.340
He seems to have studied ahead.

527
00:37:39.423 --> 00:37:42.051
You had him study ahead a lot. didn't you?

528
00:37:42.134 --> 00:37:43.678
No. not really.

529
00:37:43.761 --> 00:37:46.430
Then he must be a natural.

530
00:37:46.514 --> 00:37:49.475
I wonder if U-jin takes after you.

531
00:37:49.976 --> 00:37:51.727
You did well in school. didn't you?

532
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:54.230
-A little bit.
-I knew it.

533
00:37:54.313 --> 00:37:57.149
Ma'am. you look like you did.
You really do.

534
00:37:58.734 --> 00:38:03.281
By the way. from now on.
please don't make U-jin solve problems.

535
00:38:03.364 --> 00:38:05.658
If he doesn't know.
it could hurt his self-esteem.

536
00:38:06.242 --> 00:38:08.077
I didn't realize.

537
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:10.538
I've learned something important
thanks to you.

538
00:38:11.455 --> 00:38:14.625
Seeing that we're on the same page.
I won't have to worry this time.

539
00:38:14.709 --> 00:38:16.460
What were you worried about. ma'am?

540
00:38:16.544 --> 00:38:18.963
The previous homeroom teacher
was really strange.

541
00:38:19.046 --> 00:38:22.174
Ma'am. I will make sure
I'm never like that.

542
00:38:23.009 --> 00:38:23.843
Thank you.

543
00:38:27.638 --> 00:38:28.472
NA HWA-JIN

544
00:38:29.432 --> 00:38:30.933
Yes. what can I do for you?

545
00:38:31.017 --> 00:38:33.936
U-jin keeps dozing off during class.

546
00:38:34.020 --> 00:38:35.563
What should I do about it?

547
00:38:35.646 --> 00:38:37.273
You can just wake him.

548
00:38:37.356 --> 00:38:39.650
Sleeping is a student's right.

549
00:38:39.734 --> 00:38:42.695
Would it be okay for me to violate it?

550
00:38:42.778 --> 00:38:44.405
I'll allow it. Just wake him up.

551
00:38:44.488 --> 00:38:45.823
Yes. ma'am.

552
00:38:46.949 --> 00:38:48.951
What would be the best way to wake U-jin?

553
00:38:49.035 --> 00:38:50.328
Just shake him awake.

554
00:38:50.411 --> 00:38:53.080
I could be accused of child abuse
if I touch him.

555
00:38:53.164 --> 00:38:55.416
Then you can just call him to wake him up.

556
00:38:55.499 --> 00:38:56.709
Right!

557
00:38:56.792 --> 00:38:57.668
NA HWA-JIN

558
00:38:57.752 --> 00:39:01.756
If U-jin is startled by the loud noise
and gets emotionally stressed.

559
00:39:01.839 --> 00:39:02.798
that can be abuse…

560
00:39:02.882 --> 00:39:04.717
Then tell his neighbor to wake him.

561
00:39:04.800 --> 00:39:07.011
What if that embarrasses him?

562
00:39:07.094 --> 00:39:08.929
Don't wake him. and just leave him be.

563
00:39:09.013 --> 00:39:12.183
Ma'am. that would be neglect.
Neglect is also a form of abuse.

564
00:39:14.727 --> 00:39:16.812
<i>Hello? Ma'am?</i>

565
00:39:17.563 --> 00:39:18.606
NA HWA-JIN

566
00:39:22.777 --> 00:39:23.986
For God's sake.

567
00:39:31.660 --> 00:39:32.828
<i>Ma'am. it's me.</i>

568
00:39:32.912 --> 00:39:37.500
<i>When marking U-jin's spelling tests.</i>
<i>what should I use instead of a slash?</i>

569
00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:39.668
There are so many options.

570
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:41.087
You could use a star.

571
00:39:41.170 --> 00:39:44.256
<i>But stars are used for important things.</i>

572
00:39:44.340 --> 00:39:45.216
Or a triangle.

573
00:39:45.299 --> 00:39:48.803
<i>That's for partially correct answers.</i>

574
00:39:51.847 --> 00:39:52.681
A rhombus?

575
00:39:52.765 --> 00:39:53.682
A trapezoid.

576
00:39:54.183 --> 00:39:55.184
NA HWA-JIN

577
00:39:55.267 --> 00:39:56.227
Just…

578
00:39:58.187 --> 00:39:59.647
use a slash.

579
00:39:59.730 --> 00:40:01.482
<i>Yes. ma'am. I'll call you again.</i>

580
00:40:01.565 --> 00:40:02.817
Damn it.

581
00:40:03.859 --> 00:40:04.944
Goddamn it!

582
00:40:10.574 --> 00:40:11.992
<i>What are your thoughts</i>

583
00:40:12.076 --> 00:40:15.037
on parents contacting teachers

584
00:40:15.121 --> 00:40:16.956
on their personal numbers?

585
00:40:17.039 --> 00:40:21.252
I heard it has major implications
for teachers' rights and privacy.

586
00:40:21.335 --> 00:40:26.006
That's why we're running a pilot project
to provide work numbers for teachers.

587
00:40:26.090 --> 00:40:27.341
Will it be effective?

588
00:40:28.217 --> 00:40:29.927
Can parents actually be stopped

589
00:40:30.010 --> 00:40:34.265
from contacting teachers on social media.
via DMs. or even visiting their homes?

590
00:40:35.057 --> 00:40:38.144
We plan to set up
a complaints response team in each school

591
00:40:38.227 --> 00:40:41.522
to save teachers
from directly dealing with complaints.

592
00:40:41.605 --> 00:40:44.358
Are you saying it's fine for them
to deal with complaints?

593
00:40:44.859 --> 00:40:46.235
They're not punching bags.

594
00:40:46.318 --> 00:40:50.072
Passing complaints around
will only create another tragedy.

595
00:40:53.159 --> 00:40:56.245
You say you'll change the system
and find a solution

596
00:40:56.745 --> 00:40:59.039
every time a teacher dies at school.

597
00:40:59.123 --> 00:41:01.834
Then this should stop happening.
but why hasn't it?

598
00:41:01.917 --> 00:41:04.378
A system isn't something
you create after an incident.

599
00:41:04.462 --> 00:41:06.547
It's something you design
to prevent problems.

600
00:41:09.425 --> 00:41:11.135
Let's come up with a solution.

601
00:41:11.635 --> 00:41:14.555
If the law is needed.
I'll bring in the Minister of Justice.

602
00:41:14.638 --> 00:41:17.475
If power is needed.
I'll bring the president if I have to.

603
00:41:17.558 --> 00:41:18.601
Let's make sure

604
00:41:19.268 --> 00:41:21.187
no more teachers die

605
00:41:21.687 --> 00:41:23.105
because of complaints.

606
00:41:23.814 --> 00:41:24.857
Yes. sir.

607
00:41:38.120 --> 00:41:39.497
Ma'am!

608
00:41:39.580 --> 00:41:41.499
I was actually about to call you.

609
00:41:41.582 --> 00:41:44.710
When we wave to greet others.
we wave like this.

610
00:41:44.793 --> 00:41:47.963
Should I get the kids
to use their right hand or left hand?

611
00:41:48.047 --> 00:41:51.091
Waving is actually related
to the right and left sides of the brain.

612
00:41:51.175 --> 00:41:53.636
That's something
you can decide for yourself.

613
00:41:53.719 --> 00:41:56.889
What would a teacher know?
You would know better.

614
00:41:56.972 --> 00:41:59.391
Then what would teachers be at school for?

615
00:41:59.475 --> 00:42:01.810
I'll call you when I need to.
so please don't call.

616
00:42:02.770 --> 00:42:04.605
Then maybe I could DM you or--

617
00:42:04.688 --> 00:42:07.024
No. I'm telling you not to!

618
00:42:07.608 --> 00:42:09.777
-Yes. ma'am.
-And watch yourself.

619
00:42:10.277 --> 00:42:12.613
My husband is furious
about what happened yesterday.

620
00:42:12.696 --> 00:42:14.114
U-jin's father?

621
00:42:14.782 --> 00:42:16.534
Oh no. That shouldn't happen.

622
00:42:21.664 --> 00:42:23.874
Customer number 820.

623
00:42:24.583 --> 00:42:25.626
Yes.

624
00:42:25.709 --> 00:42:27.044
-Hello.
-Here.

625
00:42:27.127 --> 00:42:28.629
How can I help you?

626
00:42:28.712 --> 00:42:31.006
May I please speak to U-jin's father?

627
00:42:32.007 --> 00:42:33.008
Pardon?

628
00:42:34.009 --> 00:42:35.302
U-jin's father.

629
00:42:36.095 --> 00:42:37.555
U-jin's father.

630
00:42:38.055 --> 00:42:39.265
There's a second floor.

631
00:42:39.348 --> 00:42:41.183
U-jin's father!

632
00:42:41.267 --> 00:42:42.726
U-jin's fath…

633
00:42:47.106 --> 00:42:49.984
-Who are you?
-Do you happen to be U-jin's father?

634
00:42:50.818 --> 00:42:51.735
Yes. I am.

635
00:42:54.989 --> 00:42:58.033
Sir. I am very sorry.

636
00:42:58.117 --> 00:42:59.660
Please forgive me just this once.

637
00:42:59.743 --> 00:43:00.703
Please don't do this.

638
00:43:00.786 --> 00:43:04.331
I worked very hard
to become a teacher. sir.

639
00:43:05.291 --> 00:43:06.917
Are you U-jin's homeroom teacher?

640
00:43:07.001 --> 00:43:10.546
I heard you were extremely angry
because of what I did. sir.

641
00:43:10.629 --> 00:43:15.759
If you tell me what I did wrong.
I will make sure it never happens again.

642
00:43:16.760 --> 00:43:18.178
-Please just get up.
-Sir!

643
00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:20.347
Sir. is it because I put a slash

644
00:43:20.431 --> 00:43:22.850
through U-jin's wrong answers like this

645
00:43:23.350 --> 00:43:25.019
that you are so angry?

646
00:43:25.102 --> 00:43:26.312
If that's not it.

647
00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:30.524
is it because I used negative words
such as "no" and "don't" to U-jin?

648
00:43:30.608 --> 00:43:34.361
The last time you came to our school.
you almost hit the former teacher.

649
00:43:34.445 --> 00:43:36.739
It serves us right to get beaten up. sir.

650
00:43:36.822 --> 00:43:38.365
But you'll get me fired.

651
00:43:38.449 --> 00:43:40.701
Please don't take away my livelihood. sir.

652
00:43:41.869 --> 00:43:44.079
Sir. I'm begging you.

653
00:43:44.163 --> 00:43:46.373
-Let go of me.
-Gosh. please don't hit…

654
00:43:46.457 --> 00:43:47.666
-Oh my.
-What's with him?

655
00:43:48.667 --> 00:43:50.544
Sir. I am sorry.

656
00:43:51.211 --> 00:43:52.713
Sir. it's not what you think.

657
00:43:52.796 --> 00:43:53.964
Sir!

658
00:43:54.048 --> 00:43:56.133
Oh my God. How embarrassing.
What is he doing?

659
00:43:56.216 --> 00:43:57.676
-Seriously?
-Sir!

660
00:43:59.261 --> 00:44:00.095
Your pants. sir.

661
00:44:00.971 --> 00:44:02.181
-Pull your pants up.
-Damn.

662
00:44:02.264 --> 00:44:03.098
Wait.

663
00:44:03.849 --> 00:44:05.601
Do you have a death wish?

664
00:44:12.816 --> 00:44:14.610
Learn to control that temper of yours.

665
00:44:15.402 --> 00:44:18.947
If I ever hear anything
like "my husband is angry" again.

666
00:44:20.783 --> 00:44:21.742
then you're done for.

667
00:44:27.456 --> 00:44:28.540
Right then. sir.

668
00:44:29.041 --> 00:44:30.668
I'll get going now. sir.

669
00:44:33.003 --> 00:44:34.046
Damn it!

670
00:44:34.546 --> 00:44:37.466
That was embarrassing as hell!
Can't you even handle one teacher?

671
00:44:37.549 --> 00:44:38.967
How did I know he'd do that?

672
00:44:40.344 --> 00:44:43.180
I'm up for a promotion soon.
The manager saw everything. Now what?

673
00:44:43.263 --> 00:44:45.849
It was that teacher.
Why take it out on me?

674
00:44:45.933 --> 00:44:46.975
Damn you!

675
00:44:47.059 --> 00:44:48.268
You deal with this.

676
00:44:48.352 --> 00:44:50.562
Talk to the principal.
or file a complaint.

677
00:44:50.646 --> 00:44:52.064
Get the bastard fired now!

678
00:44:52.147 --> 00:44:53.232
Fine!

679
00:44:53.315 --> 00:44:54.483
Jesus.

680
00:44:55.192 --> 00:44:56.151
Damn it.

681
00:45:00.447 --> 00:45:02.783
-Hello.
-Hi. guys.

682
00:45:03.951 --> 00:45:05.994
-Hello.
-Bye. Mom.

683
00:45:06.078 --> 00:45:08.122
-Hi. children.
-Hello.

684
00:45:13.377 --> 00:45:15.754
Do you even train your teachers?

685
00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:18.215
Mr. Na caused a scene
at a parent's workplace!

686
00:45:18.298 --> 00:45:19.425
Do something.

687
00:45:23.721 --> 00:45:26.140
It's illegal for you to show up like this.

688
00:45:26.223 --> 00:45:28.726
If you would like to contact us.
use the app.

689
00:45:29.226 --> 00:45:32.604
And if you have a complaint.
please follow the proper procedure.

690
00:45:33.313 --> 00:45:34.815
If that's not enough.

691
00:45:34.898 --> 00:45:37.985
please use an online complaint board
at the Blue House.

692
00:45:38.068 --> 00:45:41.238
the Ministry of Education. or the ERPB.

693
00:45:41.822 --> 00:45:43.031
Ma'am.

694
00:45:43.115 --> 00:45:45.033
Do you think I don't know that already?

695
00:45:45.117 --> 00:45:48.454
Shall I tell you something else
you already know very well?

696
00:45:48.537 --> 00:45:50.789
U-jin may be your precious child.

697
00:45:51.832 --> 00:45:54.793
but the teachers are also

698
00:45:55.294 --> 00:45:57.254
someone's precious child.

699
00:46:01.508 --> 00:46:02.926
You're all

700
00:46:03.719 --> 00:46:05.137
out of your minds.

701
00:46:05.220 --> 00:46:07.890
You'll regret this. Just you wait.

702
00:46:18.317 --> 00:46:20.194
<i>The ERPB will take responsibility</i>

703
00:46:20.778 --> 00:46:22.488
and deal with any consequences.

704
00:46:22.571 --> 00:46:24.656
So when things like this happen.

705
00:46:25.240 --> 00:46:29.161
please be the teachers' mentor.
not their principal.

706
00:46:31.330 --> 00:46:34.541
Right now. the teachers need

707
00:46:34.625 --> 00:46:36.710
a mentor like you…

708
00:46:38.712 --> 00:46:40.506
more than they need the ERPB.

709
00:46:54.394 --> 00:46:55.437
He's right.

710
00:46:57.439 --> 00:46:58.732
We were their mentors.

711
00:47:02.152 --> 00:47:03.153
Sometimes.

712
00:47:04.571 --> 00:47:06.073
I seem to forget.

713
00:47:13.038 --> 00:47:14.498
What have you drawn here?

714
00:47:15.290 --> 00:47:16.834
U-jin. come with me.

715
00:47:17.501 --> 00:47:18.335
We're done here.

716
00:47:20.671 --> 00:47:21.713
Get up.

717
00:47:27.845 --> 00:47:28.929
Get up!

718
00:47:39.731 --> 00:47:41.149
Gather the parents for me.

719
00:47:41.233 --> 00:47:43.402
This is absurd.
I'll tell you when we meet.

720
00:47:51.702 --> 00:47:53.412
You're all here.

721
00:48:02.212 --> 00:48:03.922
Why are you here?

722
00:48:04.006 --> 00:48:05.507
Hello. ma'am.

723
00:48:06.049 --> 00:48:07.050
Well…

724
00:48:11.013 --> 00:48:12.639
I came to give you this.

725
00:48:13.223 --> 00:48:14.600
What is this?

726
00:48:14.683 --> 00:48:16.727
If you take a look…

727
00:48:17.978 --> 00:48:20.272
COMPLAINT
COMPLAINANT: NA HWA-JIN

728
00:48:20.355 --> 00:48:23.984
I filed a complaint against you
for child abuse.

729
00:48:24.067 --> 00:48:25.736
-Child abuse?
-Yes.

730
00:48:25.819 --> 00:48:27.195
I saw everything.

731
00:48:27.779 --> 00:48:29.907
U-jin didn't want to.

732
00:48:29.990 --> 00:48:31.909
but you grabbed him
and held him like this.

733
00:48:31.992 --> 00:48:35.913
When he was changing into his gym clothes.
he had bruises all over his body and--

734
00:48:35.996 --> 00:48:37.247
Where on my child's body

735
00:48:38.707 --> 00:48:40.208
are you saying there are bruises?

736
00:48:40.292 --> 00:48:43.754
Well. we'll find out
once the police investigate.

737
00:48:43.837 --> 00:48:46.840
What gives you the right
to report me. his parent?

738
00:48:46.924 --> 00:48:50.052
"When a teacher becomes aware of
or suspects child abuse

739
00:48:50.135 --> 00:48:53.013
in the course of performing their duties.

740
00:48:53.096 --> 00:48:55.015
the teacher shall immediately report it

741
00:48:55.098 --> 00:48:57.726
to a child protection agency
or an investigative agency."

742
00:48:58.685 --> 00:48:59.645
That's the law.

743
00:49:00.437 --> 00:49:01.813
What if it's not child abuse?

744
00:49:02.606 --> 00:49:04.066
Then I'll have to apologize.

745
00:49:05.525 --> 00:49:07.486
That's the law.

746
00:49:13.867 --> 00:49:17.287
I heard this mom
bullied Ms. Choi Ji-seon. didn't she?

747
00:49:17.371 --> 00:49:21.124
It was so bad. the teacher developed
partial facial paralysis.

748
00:49:21.708 --> 00:49:23.919
She's not well enough
to come to school now.

749
00:49:24.002 --> 00:49:25.379
-Really?
-I knew it.

750
00:49:25.462 --> 00:49:27.714
I heard she's been extreme
since kindergarten.

751
00:49:27.798 --> 00:49:29.591
No wonder the kid is odd.

752
00:49:29.675 --> 00:49:31.927
Yes. it's a relief
he's not in my child's class.

753
00:49:32.010 --> 00:49:33.553
-I know. right?
-Who said that?

754
00:49:34.054 --> 00:49:35.597
U-jin's mom.

755
00:49:35.681 --> 00:49:36.848
I asked who said that.

756
00:49:36.932 --> 00:49:39.601
No one said it. On the Internet. it…

757
00:49:39.685 --> 00:49:41.061
Was it that bitch. Ms. Choi?

758
00:49:43.105 --> 00:49:44.731
-I'm asking you!
-Oh my.

759
00:49:44.815 --> 00:49:46.858
Was it that bitch of a teacher.
Choi Ji-seon?

760
00:49:48.735 --> 00:49:49.695
So-yun.

761
00:49:49.778 --> 00:49:52.030
-Let's go.
-I'd better go too.

762
00:49:57.202 --> 00:50:00.539
U-JIN'S MOTHER

763
00:50:18.932 --> 00:50:20.392
Damn it.

764
00:50:21.601 --> 00:50:22.519
Damn it.

765
00:51:02.142 --> 00:51:03.727
Were you two in on it together?

766
00:51:05.771 --> 00:51:08.356
Don't you know U-jin is being left out
because of you?

767
00:51:08.440 --> 00:51:10.859
Why the hell is the teacher at fault?
That's on you.

768
00:51:10.942 --> 00:51:11.902
Excuse me?

769
00:51:11.985 --> 00:51:14.237
-Are you being rude to a parent right now?
-What?

770
00:51:14.321 --> 00:51:16.114
You're rude. Why can't I be?

771
00:51:17.783 --> 00:51:21.661
I'll report you and that bitch
to the Office of Education and the press.

772
00:51:21.745 --> 00:51:23.163
Oh. and the ERPB.

773
00:51:23.705 --> 00:51:25.290
My family works there.

774
00:51:25.874 --> 00:51:28.043
I'll see to it that you never teach again.

775
00:51:29.795 --> 00:51:31.254
Allow me to reintroduce myself.

776
00:51:32.547 --> 00:51:35.300
I'm Inspector Na Hwa-jin from the ERPB.

777
00:51:36.635 --> 00:51:39.721
I am well aware of what you did
to Ms. Choi.

778
00:51:39.805 --> 00:51:41.139
That's why we are here.

779
00:51:41.223 --> 00:51:42.307
Isn't this entrapment?

780
00:51:43.266 --> 00:51:44.976
Entrapment is illegal!

781
00:51:45.060 --> 00:51:46.812
You love the law. don't you?

782
00:51:46.895 --> 00:51:48.105
Shall we do it legally?

783
00:51:48.188 --> 00:51:50.440
The ERPB investigation finds you liable

784
00:51:50.524 --> 00:51:53.527
of criminal penalties
for malicious false complaints.

785
00:51:53.610 --> 00:51:55.237
violation of teachers' rights.

786
00:51:55.320 --> 00:51:57.239
obstruction of business. and insult.

787
00:51:57.322 --> 00:51:58.740
What did I do wrong?

788
00:51:58.824 --> 00:52:00.700
It was all for my child's sake.

789
00:52:00.784 --> 00:52:04.412
What kind of parent in the world
would just watch their child being harmed?

790
00:52:04.496 --> 00:52:06.790
It's all Choi's fault.

791
00:52:06.873 --> 00:52:08.834
What does she know about education
with no kids?

792
00:52:09.709 --> 00:52:11.711
How would she know how a parent feels?

793
00:52:14.673 --> 00:52:18.009
Then you'd know very well
how Ms. Choi's parents feel.

794
00:52:19.136 --> 00:52:23.140
How do you think her mother felt
watching her daughter suffer?

795
00:52:24.850 --> 00:52:25.684
I don't know.

796
00:52:26.184 --> 00:52:28.019
Who cares what happens to that bitch?

797
00:52:28.520 --> 00:52:29.980
Only my child matters to me.

798
00:52:30.564 --> 00:52:32.649
All the parents in the world are the same.

799
00:52:37.195 --> 00:52:39.865
Are you sure this looks like me?

800
00:52:40.490 --> 00:52:42.159
Are you? Wait.

801
00:52:42.242 --> 00:52:47.289
I don't think the skin tone
matches mine. U-jin.

802
00:52:48.540 --> 00:52:50.000
I'll draw too.

803
00:52:52.502 --> 00:52:53.461
U-jin.

804
00:52:54.880 --> 00:52:58.967
Why did you call me on your mom's phone?

805
00:52:59.467 --> 00:53:01.553
You told me

806
00:53:01.636 --> 00:53:03.972
I should do what my heart tells me.

807
00:53:04.723 --> 00:53:08.602
I was having a hard time.
so I wanted to see you.

808
00:53:12.272 --> 00:53:14.858
Why were you having a hard time?

809
00:53:18.236 --> 00:53:20.238
I'm sorry. Ms. Choi.

810
00:53:20.739 --> 00:53:23.575
My mom hurt you a lot. didn't she?

811
00:53:28.413 --> 00:53:29.497
U-jin.

812
00:53:31.666 --> 00:53:33.335
It's not up to you to apologize.

813
00:53:39.966 --> 00:53:42.594
HOME OF THE HEART

814
00:53:42.677 --> 00:53:44.846
Mom hates me.

815
00:53:45.513 --> 00:53:47.515
She doesn't smile at me

816
00:53:47.599 --> 00:53:49.601
and always looks angry.

817
00:53:53.855 --> 00:53:55.148
Come here. U-jin.

818
00:53:58.860 --> 00:54:02.405
You must have had a really tough time.

819
00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:04.032
It's okay.

820
00:54:05.116 --> 00:54:06.785
It's all right.

821
00:54:10.997 --> 00:54:12.207
You're okay.

822
00:54:21.049 --> 00:54:22.801
Do you feel a little better now?

823
00:54:25.136 --> 00:54:27.138
Shall we get back to coloring this in?

824
00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:35.981
Who do you think
truly cares for the child?

825
00:54:43.071 --> 00:54:46.199
What kind of adult
do you hope U-jin grows up to be?

826
00:54:47.075 --> 00:54:50.704
The kind who does not apologize.
even when he's wrong?

827
00:54:51.955 --> 00:54:55.875
The kind who lives a lonely life
with no friends or colleagues?

828
00:54:58.795 --> 00:55:03.049
The kind who treats others' lives
as worthless if it serves their own gain?

829
00:55:03.717 --> 00:55:05.302
That's not what you want.

830
00:55:06.219 --> 00:55:07.887
So please stop.

831
00:55:08.722 --> 00:55:10.473
Your child doesn't like it.

832
00:55:10.974 --> 00:55:12.892
He says he likes his teacher.

833
00:55:13.393 --> 00:55:14.769
Please trust U-jin

834
00:55:16.146 --> 00:55:17.897
and trust his teacher.

835
00:55:19.941 --> 00:55:23.028
Hey. you can't draw it like this.

836
00:55:24.237 --> 00:55:25.739
Do you think it looks like me?

837
00:55:26.906 --> 00:55:27.824
Do you?

838
00:55:27.907 --> 00:55:30.160
Why can't you answer me. U-jin?

839
00:55:30.952 --> 00:55:32.203
I think it looks like me.

840
00:55:32.287 --> 00:55:35.206
I'll be the rabbit. You be the bear.

841
00:55:41.254 --> 00:55:42.756
That's a great drawing.

842
00:55:47.552 --> 00:55:50.597
How did you know
Ms. Choi would come to the school?

843
00:55:50.680 --> 00:55:51.973
Because she's a teacher.

844
00:55:52.724 --> 00:55:54.517
School came to my mind first.

845
00:55:55.602 --> 00:55:57.645
I guess it was the same for Ms. Choi too.

846
00:55:57.729 --> 00:56:00.190
So you two were telepathic.

847
00:56:00.273 --> 00:56:01.983
Maybe.

848
00:56:02.817 --> 00:56:05.945
By any chance.
do you both know what telepathy is?

849
00:56:06.029 --> 00:56:08.239
Isn't it when you think the same
as someone else?

850
00:56:08.323 --> 00:56:10.283
No. it's not simply thinking the same.

851
00:56:10.367 --> 00:56:12.827
It's when a person's thoughts and actions

852
00:56:12.911 --> 00:56:15.747
are passed on to someone else.

853
00:56:15.830 --> 00:56:17.916
It's like a kind of superpower.

854
00:56:17.999 --> 00:56:20.710
They're just lucky guesses.
A superpower is a stretch.

855
00:56:20.794 --> 00:56:22.504
No. telepathy is really real.

856
00:56:22.587 --> 00:56:24.589
-Can you prove it?
-Of course.

857
00:56:25.173 --> 00:56:26.007
Okay. then.

858
00:56:26.549 --> 00:56:29.803
Look into my eyes and think of a word.
I'll guess what it is.

859
00:56:29.886 --> 00:56:31.096
For God's sake.

860
00:56:42.982 --> 00:56:43.983
Done. Take a guess.

861
00:56:46.403 --> 00:56:47.237
Eye booger.

862
00:56:47.821 --> 00:56:49.406
What? Eye booger?

863
00:56:49.906 --> 00:56:52.617
You're wrong. You didn't get it.
You can't do anything.

864
00:56:53.118 --> 00:56:56.788
No. I meant
you've got a huge eye booger in there.

865
00:57:00.583 --> 00:57:02.836
You have an eye booger.
That's embarrassing.

866
00:57:02.919 --> 00:57:03.920
I've got it out.

867
00:57:05.880 --> 00:57:07.173
So what do you want to eat?

868
00:57:07.257 --> 00:57:08.341
-<i>Jokbal</i>.
-<i>Jokbal </i>or…

869
00:57:08.842 --> 00:57:10.468
Oh wow.

870
00:57:10.552 --> 00:57:12.971
Amazing. This is what I'm talking about.

871
00:57:13.054 --> 00:57:14.931
That's the word I thought of earlier.

872
00:57:15.014 --> 00:57:16.558
Now. that's telepathy.

873
00:57:16.641 --> 00:57:18.393
See? I told you it's real.

874
00:57:18.476 --> 00:57:19.436
Try it again.

875
00:57:19.519 --> 00:57:22.355
This time. think of a color…

876
00:57:22.439 --> 00:57:25.400
Let's assume there are two people.
A and B.

877
00:57:26.067 --> 00:57:30.238
A used their position to threaten B.

878
00:57:30.321 --> 00:57:32.449
obstruct B's exercise of rights.

879
00:57:32.532 --> 00:57:34.534
and force B to do things
outside their role.

880
00:57:35.118 --> 00:57:38.079
<i>This falls under Article 324.</i>
<i>Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act</i>

881
00:57:38.163 --> 00:57:41.583
<i>as a crime of coercion and is punishable</i>
<i>by up to five years' imprisonment</i>

882
00:57:41.666 --> 00:57:43.376
or a fine of up to 30 million won.

883
00:57:43.460 --> 00:57:44.294
DEFENDANT

884
00:57:44.377 --> 00:57:45.253
Furthermore.

885
00:57:45.753 --> 00:57:49.424
A kept snooping on B's social media.
left malicious comments.

886
00:57:49.507 --> 00:57:51.384
<i>and even commented on B's underwear.</i>

887
00:57:51.468 --> 00:57:54.220
<i>causing B to feel disgust</i>
<i>and sexual humiliation.</i>

888
00:57:54.304 --> 00:57:58.308
A persistently messaged B
and turned up at B's home.

889
00:57:58.391 --> 00:58:01.352
causing B to feel fear and anxiety.

890
00:58:01.853 --> 00:58:05.148
This can constitute stalking
and is a crime

891
00:58:05.231 --> 00:58:07.567
under the Punishment
of Crime of Stalking Act.

892
00:58:07.650 --> 00:58:10.612
punishable by
up to three years' imprisonment

893
00:58:10.695 --> 00:58:11.988
or a fine of 30 million won.

894
00:58:12.906 --> 00:58:15.492
Moreover. with the intent to induce fear.

895
00:58:15.575 --> 00:58:19.579
person A utilized an acquaintance
to attempt an assault on person B.

896
00:58:19.662 --> 00:58:23.500
which falls under Article 283.
Paragraph 1 of the Criminal Act.

897
00:58:24.083 --> 00:58:28.630
This is subject to a fine of up to
five million won or three years in prison.

898
00:58:33.801 --> 00:58:37.347
With such conduct ongoing.
B fell into depression.

899
00:58:37.430 --> 00:58:39.224
<i>suffered a nervous breakdown.</i>

900
00:58:39.307 --> 00:58:41.726
<i>and even made an extreme decision</i>
<i>to harm themselves.</i>

901
00:58:42.685 --> 00:58:44.479
This is also an undeniable crime.

902
00:58:44.562 --> 00:58:48.274
constituting assault and battery.
causing bodily harm.

903
00:58:50.652 --> 00:58:52.612
A is the defendant.

904
00:58:53.112 --> 00:58:53.947
and B is

905
00:58:55.073 --> 00:58:56.282
Ms. Choi Ji-seon.

906
00:59:00.870 --> 00:59:03.581
These actions are undeniable crimes

907
00:59:03.665 --> 00:59:05.875
when they occur between persons.

908
00:59:06.543 --> 00:59:09.337
So why are they allowed
between a teacher and a parent?

909
00:59:20.056 --> 00:59:21.599
<i>We have learned</i>

910
00:59:21.683 --> 00:59:24.727
that repeated. constant.
and malicious parental complaints

911
00:59:24.811 --> 00:59:27.188
place undue pressure on innocent teachers

912
00:59:27.272 --> 00:59:31.651
and even deprive them of the opportunity
to become good teachers.

913
00:59:31.734 --> 00:59:34.279
In the future.
when a teacher is reported for child abuse

914
00:59:34.362 --> 00:59:36.072
or a malicious complaint is filed.

915
00:59:36.155 --> 00:59:39.325
the ERPB will dispatch
an inspector on-site

916
00:59:39.409 --> 00:59:41.661
to determine the facts.

917
00:59:41.744 --> 00:59:43.538
If the teacher is found innocent.

918
00:59:44.205 --> 00:59:48.293
we promise to fight together
with the teachers.

919
00:59:49.294 --> 00:59:53.923
As the term "teacher-student relationship"
loses its meaning in today's age.

920
00:59:54.007 --> 00:59:56.342
we ask parents to cooperate

921
00:59:56.426 --> 01:00:00.305
so that the few remaining true educators
do not end up leaving the profession.

922
01:00:00.972 --> 01:00:04.392
We will also establish an annual
health check-up system for teachers.

923
01:00:04.475 --> 01:00:07.061
which will include support and treatment

924
01:00:07.145 --> 01:00:10.648
for those experiencing
psychological difficulties.

925
01:00:27.665 --> 01:00:29.334
To the teachers

926
01:00:29.834 --> 01:00:32.837
who ended their own lives
due to teachers' rights violations

927
01:00:33.338 --> 01:00:34.464
and

928
01:00:35.506 --> 01:00:38.551
to the teachers
who are currently suffering.

929
01:00:39.469 --> 01:00:43.056
on behalf of the Ministry of Education.

930
01:00:43.973 --> 01:00:45.516
I offer my sincere apology.

931
01:00:47.226 --> 01:00:49.270
Due to the failures
of the educational system.

932
01:00:49.937 --> 01:00:51.439
you were left unprotected…

933
01:00:53.858 --> 01:00:55.735
and were made to suffer in silence.

934
01:00:56.694 --> 01:00:58.029
I apologize.

935
01:01:20.927 --> 01:01:23.096
That's it. Well done.

936
01:01:25.640 --> 01:01:26.766
Can you receive…

937
01:01:30.645 --> 01:01:32.355
Yes!

938
01:02:25.241 --> 01:02:27.076
MOCK CSAT
PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT SUPPLIES

939
01:02:27.160 --> 01:02:29.620
MIDTERM EXAM MARKING
OPEN CLASS PREPARATION

940
01:02:32.457 --> 01:02:34.876
WEDDING DAY

941
01:02:38.337 --> 01:02:41.007
IT'S BEEN TWO WEEKS
SINCE COMING TO SCHOOL WITH GYU-CHEOL

942
01:02:41.090 --> 01:02:42.550
MY HEART FELT HEAVY THIS MORNING

943
01:02:42.633 --> 01:02:43.968
GYU-CHEOL HAS BEEN ON MY MIND

944
01:02:45.094 --> 01:02:47.680
WE HAD CAREERS COUNSELING
BUT GYU-CHEOL HAS NO DREAMS

945
01:02:56.731 --> 01:03:00.067
WHAT SHOULD I DO… ABOUT GYU-CHEOL?

946
01:03:04.989 --> 01:03:10.036
WILL I EVER BE ABLE TO… FORGIVE GYU-CHEOL?

947
01:04:15.685 --> 01:04:18.646
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

948
01:04:19.305 --> 01:05:19.239
